task.summary: The content script and background script are set up. Text simhash works. Dom not yet. Commiting to move to bitbucket.

Stay on github. The basic capability of this cloaking fighter is complete. The workflow includes the following steps: 1. look at current url and referer, to see whether it is an interesting page (from google.com and is not google.com) 2. if interesting, send it to the background script to see whether it is whitelisted or not. 3. if not, compute the simhash and send it to background script. 4. the background script fetches spider copy and computes distance between spider and user view, if distance is too large, show warning. o.w. ignore.
Previous version is not requesting webpage with spider user agent. Fixed this bug. Added progress track to project.
Added support for login page detection. The logic is that: if user has cookie for current page and the spider copy contains keyword "log in", then skip it.
Add support for redirect cloaking detection.

This seems the version that works. The popup menu is still missing though. Changes here are 1. add support for status code 2. store search cache url in background script for each tab 3. change detecting strategy. If current page has search cache, try fetch it and compute verdict, if fetch fails, fallback to the normal url fetch.
Add mode selection to cloaker catcher and refactor the code.
Modify the simhash implementation to be the same as server side (python implementation).
Implemented the online version. Should be able to detect now.
Modify the model detection to hierarchical clustering.
The cloaking detection plugin online version is working.
